<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="424" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">835.796/11–2145: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-21">November 21,
                                1945</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1647. Following release has been made to press with regard to United
                            States policy on release of aviation equipment to authorized Argentine
                            purchasers: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“The United States will release aviation equipment, including
                                    aircraft engines and personal and civilian type aircraft and
                                    parts, to authorized Argentine purchasers.</p>
                                <p>Export licenses so granted will be subject to the specific
                                    requirement that the equipment acquired will be used exclusively
                                    for civilian use in the development of private and commercial
                                    civil aviation in Argentina.</p>
                                <p>This action results exclusively from the progressive termination
                                    of war-time restrictions and is totally unrelated to any
                                    political considerations.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>